🌊 Intelligent Wetland Water Quality Prediction System
A machine learning-based system for predicting outlet water quality parameters in constructed wetlands using environmental and inlet conditions.
This project provides interactive Streamlit dashboards for real-time prediction, data analysis, and model evaluation.
🚀 Key Features
📊 Interactive dashboards using Streamlit
🤖 Machine Learning models for accurate prediction
🌦️ Incorporates weather & environmental parameters
📈 Built-in data visualization and performance metrics
📂 Supports both default datasets and user-uploaded data
🧠 Applications
🔹 1. BOD Predictor
A focused application for predicting Biochemical Oxygen Demand (BOD) at the outlet.
Model Used: ExtraTreesRegressor
Inputs:
Weeks
Inlet BOD
Temperature
Rainfall
Wind Speed
Humidity
Outputs:
Predicted Outlet BOD
Treatment Efficiency
Water Quality Status
Modules:
Dashboard
Data Upload
Model Performance
Reports
🔹 2. Wastewater Quality Predictor
A comprehensive system predicting multiple water-quality parameters.
Modl Used: RandomForestRegressor (separate model per parameter)
Inputs:
Inlet BOD, COD, TDS, EC
NH₄, NO₃, DO, pH
Weather parameters
Outputs:
Outlet BOD, COD, TDS, EC
NH₄, NO₃, DO, pH
Modules:
Data Analysis
Model Training
Prediction
Performance Evaluation
